You have several mistakes in your PHP code.

First the for loop definition isn&#39;t quite right, and by iterating to `100`, you&#39;ll get undefined index errors, because you&#39;re traversing beyond the length of the `$str` variable.

Next, `$str[$i]` will return you the character at that index of the string. It won&#39;t give you the character ASCII value. You are therefore essentially trying the arthimetic `L - 2`, `q - 2`, `g - 2`, etc.

To get the ASCII value of a character you will need to use the `ord()` function. You can then modify the ASCII value, and convert it back to a character string using the `chr()` function.

Here&#39;s a working example of what you&#39;re trying to achieve.

    $str = &#39;Lqgococ&#39;;
    
    for($i = 0; $i &lt; strlen($str); $i++) {
        $str[$i] = chr(ord($str[$i]) - 2);
    }
    
    echo $str;  // Joemama

